1.	Community differences
•	How can the users be categorised?
•	How do the categories differ from one another?
•	Is the Congress Twitter network structurally centralised around a few dominant members?
•	Does the network exhibit high degree centralisation or betweenness centralisation?
We could potentially compare Democratic vs Republic, Senate vs House, etc.
2.	Focus on influence
•	Who are the most influential users, and why?
•	Is there an imbalance of influence where influence is not reciprocated?
•	Are the influential users balanced across parties?
We can use statistics we learnt in class to examine the centrality and network structure.
3.	Cross-party influence
•	To what extent are there cross-party influence?
•	Are there any critical bridging nodes that act as articulation point?
•	Is there a stronger influence within the same party?
We could potentially evaluate within-group influence vs cross-party influence.
